<!DOcTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>User Tracking</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel = "stylesheet" href ="styles/main.css">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
</head>
<body>
    <div class ="presentation">
        <h1>Welcome dear user from <%=country%></h1>
    </div>
    <div class ="info">
        <h2>We know a lot about you hehehe.</h2>
        <p>We know your IP address: <%=ip%></p>
        <p>We know your city: <%=city%></p>
        <p>We know your region: <%=region%></p>
        <p>We know your country: <%=country%></p>
        <p>We know your postal code: <%=postalCode%></p>
        <p>We know your location: <%=coords%></p>
        <p>We know your internet provider: <%=internetProvider%></p>
        <p>We know the browser you're using: <%=browser%></p>
        <p>We know what device you're using: <%=device%></p>
        <p>We know the language of your browser: <%=language%></p>
        <p>We know what's your operating system: <%=os%></p>
    </div>
    <div class = "warning">
        <h2>Warning</h2>
        <p>This was a little reminder that you must never click on any link you see on internet.</p>
        <p>Be careful with your data, it is very valuable. Take care.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-note">
        <img src="/images/whisper-img.png" alt="Privacy Icon" width="200">
        <p><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Don't worry, we do not store or share your information. ðŸ¤«</p>
        <p>This page is just a reminder of how much your browser reveals by default.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>